Tuesday, July 28, 2009
Strongholds
So here's the deal with strongholds. First and foremost, the current idea for strongholds stemmed from the old siege weapons. While wonderful, they truly didn't have an impact on the game world or any fight in which they were used. Strongholds (originally called minifort resources) is an effort to create a strategy game within the world of SOI. To give the player a feeling a value and importance in each and every fight. Kite always gives the same example when talking about this, and it's a good one so I'll use it as well. The Fall of Osgiliath was [SPOILER ALERT] scripted. -Nothing- the players did affected it's outcome at all. Rubbish I know right? We don't want this anymore, so Kite wrote a huge scope/idea document about it. I had the unfortunate pleasure of reading the entire thing. It was written back when SoI didn't have a code team. In fact, it didn't even have a coder. It was going to be done completely with progs. This idea was scrapped in lieu of code and Grommit began his work. Shortly into it though, RL got a hold of him and he had to step down. I was then given the task to complete this project by the deadline of June 19th. I had begun collaborating with VM on the project when Case returned to our programming team. I'll be the first to admit that she has way more experience and knowledge then I do when it comes to programming, and she requested the stronghold project. I gave it to her. She stepped down from the team for reasons I will not get into in this post and we again did not have stronghold code. It was at this point we knew we'd never reach the deadline. Shortly after all this, stability became the main focus and Strongholds got pushed to progs once again. In the hands of Bangarang, and you all know the story there. It's why you are reading this in the first place. It is now once again in the coders hands and we -are- going to finish it as soon as physically possible. We are striving for excellence here. I promise that the delay will be well worth the wait. Please be patient with us, Strongholds are coming...

I stand corrected. Thank you Case, for your comment and your hard work. Well, since he is lead now we will just wait on his word whether or not we shall continue to work forward with our own version.

- Vader
